## Plan: Normalize product image presentation

Make all 6 product images appear visually uniform by giving each card's image area a clean white background, consistent aspect ratio, and consistent padding so the products float at the same apparent size.

### Change (single file: `src/routes/index.tsx`)

In the routine card markup, update the image container:

- Background: swap `bg-accent/40` → `bg-white` (with a subtle `ring-1 ring-border/40` so the white card still reads against the off-white page).
- Aspect ratio: keep `aspect-[4/3]` (already uniform).
- Image: keep `object-contain`, bump padding to `p-10 md:p-14` so smaller products (brush, oil bottles) don't look tiny next to the bonnets, and add `mx-auto max-h-full max-w-full` to lock perceived size.

That's it — no per-product overrides, no asset re-edits. Same container + same padding + white bg = uniform look.

### Not doing

- Not re-generating or editing the uploaded product photos (they already have white/near-white backgrounds).
- No layout, copy, or routing changes.
